Ensure your website has a clear and well-structured hierarchy using proper HTML tags like <h1>, <h2>, <p>, etc.
Use descriptive and keyword-rich page titles and headings.
Incorporate relevant keywords naturally throughout your content, including in paragraphs, headings, and image alt tags.
Optimize your website's loading speed by compressing images, minifying CSS and JavaScript files, and using caching techniques.
Make your website mobile-friendly and responsive to different screen sizes.
Implement proper meta tags, including the title, description, and relevant keywords.
Use clean URLs with descriptive keywords instead of generic or random strings.
Ensure your website is accessible to search engine crawlers by avoiding excessive use of JavaScript-based content or Flash elements.
